Here is my rough understanding of the thinking behind OpenAI=E2=80=99s  goo=
fy corporate structure:
=09OpenAI wants to lead the world in the development of artificial general =
intelligence (AGI), a somewhat vague=C2=A0concept that we can roughly under=
stand to mean =E2=80=9Ca computer that can think like a human but much bett=
er.=E2=80=9D Done right, AGI will usher humanity into a paradise of leisure=
 and plenty. Done wrong, AGI will impoverish or enslave or murder all of hu=
manity. Very important to get it right!=09Therefore, in developing AGI, Ope=
nAI=E2=80=99s decisions must be made by=C2=A0people who are pure of heart. =
They can never let short-term commercial considerations override their comm=
itment to the good of humanity, because what they are doing is too importan=
t.=09Developing AGI =E2=80=94 buying processors, training models =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0will be  extraordinarily expensive, costing perhaps  literally trilli=
ons of dollars. So OpenAI will need to raise a lot of money from investors.=
=09Developing AGI will also require hiring the best researchers (and fundra=
isers!) in a hotly competitive market, so OpenAI will need to be able to pa=
y and motivate them.=09Done=C2=A0the wrong way, AGI could be enormously luc=
rative for the company that develops it
  [4]
: You could raise trillions of dollars by promising investors a share of th=
e spoils of AGI, and you could motivate researchers by giving them options =
on those spoils.=09But OpenAI is committed to doing it the right way, so th=
at=E2=80=99s out. Its mission is to develop AGI for the benefit of humanity=
, not to enrich its employees or investors.=09On the other hand, OpenAI is =
not, like, launching AGI tomorrow. And=C2=A0along the way=C2=A0to AGI, ther=
e will be plenty of ways to get rich off of the artificial intelligence=C2=
=A0industry. Large language model chatbots have obvious commercial uses now=
, and OpenAI isn=E2=80=99t committed to distributing=C2=A0those=C2=A0for th=
e benefit of humanity;=C2=A0those=C2=A0it can charge for. Those trillions o=
f dollars of chips that will be needed to build AGI? Someone=E2=80=99s gonn=
a make a profit on those chips, and maybe OpenAI can get some of that.=09Al=
l that ancillary stuff =E2=80=94=C2=A0all the money that will slosh around =
the artificial intelligence business while OpenAI methodically works toward=
 its goal of building AGI =E2=80=94=C2=A0can be carved up and used to attra=
ct investors and motivate employees.=09OpenAI, at its core, doesn=E2=80=99t=
 need any of that. It=E2=80=99s not motivated by money, as an entity; it=E2=
=80=99s motivated by the good of humanity.=09So there=E2=80=99s a trade: Op=
enAI can raise money (and attract employees) for=C2=A0its grand project by =
distributing the intermediate spoils to investors and employees. OpenAI doe=
sn=E2=80=99t want those spoils. It just wants the ultimate goal, the AGI, w=
hich it will use benevolently to usher in a golden age for humanity.

I am exaggerating in places, and I am not saying that any of this is correc=
t. I am just saying that, from the outside, this model seems to explain a l=
ot of OpenAI=E2=80=99s choices. We have talked about many of them:
=09OpenAI is officially a   nonprofit organization with no shareholders at =
all.=09But it has raised billions of dollars from investors, led by Microso=
ft Corp., through its for-profit subsidiary.=09But that subsidiary is actua=
lly a =E2=80=9Ccapped-profit=E2=80=9D company: Investors can make a profit =
on their investment, but   not an infinite one; once they=E2=80=99ve gotten=
 enough profit to make their investment worth their while, OpenAI no longer=
 has to try to make profits for them, and can focus on humanity.=09Similarl=
y OpenAI=E2=80=99s employees get  capped-profit quasi-shares, to motivate t=
hem to build AI, but not to motivate them to put their dreams of dynastic w=
ealth above the good of humanity.=09But OpenAI=E2=80=99s=C2=A0board of dire=
ctors, who are ultimately in charge of making sure it benefits rather than =
enslaves humanity,=C2=A0don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0get stock (or options, or quasi-=
stock): Their motives are pure. Even Sam Altman, OpenAI=E2=80=99s founder a=
nd chief executive officer, doesn=E2=80=99t own any stock.
  [5]

=09OpenAI also has a commercial partnership with Microsoft giving it access=
 to OpenAI=E2=80=99s models=C2=A0up to=C2=A0(but not including) AGI. Once O=
penAI builds AGI, that=E2=80=99s for humanity, not for Microsoft.

Here=E2=80=99s another one that=C2=A0Axios=E2=80=99s Dan Primack  reported=
=C2=A0today:

OpenAI Startup Fund was launched in late 2021 to invest in other AI startup=
