<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is my rough understanding of the thinking=
 behind OpenAI=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/34364292.279392/aHR0cHM6Ly9vcGVuYWkuY29tL291ci1zdHJ1Y3R1cmU/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB5913f27b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> goofy corporate structure</a>:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">OpenAI wants to lead the world in the=
 development of artificial general intelligence (AGI), a somewhat vague=C2=
=A0concept that we can roughly understand to mean =E2=80=9Ca computer that =
can think like a human but much better.=E2=80=9D Done right, AGI will usher=
 humanity into a paradise of leisure and plenty. Done wrong, AGI will impov=
erish or enslave or murder all of humanity. Very important to get it right!=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Therefore, in developing AGI, Ope=
nAI=E2=80=99s decisions must be made by=C2=A0people who are pure of heart. =
They can never let short-term commercial considerations override their comm=
itment to the good of humanity, because what they are doing is too importan=
t.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Developing AGI =E2=80=94 buying=
 processors, training models =E2=80=94=C2=A0will be <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34364292.279392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL=
2NvbnRlbnQvNjMxNGQ3OGQtODFmMy00M2Y1LTlkYWYtYjEwZjNmZjllMjRm/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB538eddb9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> extraordinarily expensive</a>, costing perha=
ps <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34364292.279392=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS90ZWNoL2FpL3NhbS1hbHRtYW4tc2Vla3MtdHJpbGxpb25zLW=
9mLWRvbGxhcnMtdG8tcmVzaGFwZS1idXNpbmVzcy1vZi1jaGlwcy1hbmQtYWktODlhYjNkYjA/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5d085244" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> literally trillions of dollars</=
a>. So OpenAI will need to raise a lot of money from investors.</li>=09<li =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Developing AGI will also require hiring the b=
est researchers (and fundraisers!) in a hotly competitive market, so OpenAI=
 will need to be able to pay and motivate them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">Done=C2=A0<em>the wrong way</em>, AGI could be enormously luc=
rative for the company that develops it<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"=
#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: n=
one !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-b=
lock;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>: You could raise trillions of dollars by promising investors a share o=
f the spoils of AGI, and you could motivate researchers by giving them opti=
ons on those spoils.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But OpenAI is=
 committed to doing it the right way, so that=E2=80=99s out. Its mission is=
 to develop AGI for the benefit of humanity, not to enrich its employees or=
 investors.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">On the other hand, Ope=
nAI is not, like, launching AGI tomorrow. And=C2=A0<em>along the way</em>=
=C2=A0to AGI, there will be plenty of ways to get rich off of the artificia=
l intelligence=C2=A0industry. Large language model chatbots have obvious co=
mmercial uses now, and OpenAI isn=E2=80=99t committed to distributing=C2=A0=
<em>those=C2=A0</em>for the benefit of humanity;=C2=A0<em>those=C2=A0</em>i=
t can charge for. Those trillions of dollars of chips that will be needed t=
o build AGI? Someone=E2=80=99s gonna make a profit on those chips, and mayb=
e OpenAI can get some of that.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">All=
 that ancillary stuff =E2=80=94=C2=A0all the money that will slosh around t=
he artificial intelligence business while OpenAI methodically works toward =
its goal of building AGI =E2=80=94=C2=A0can be carved up and used to attrac=
t investors and motivate employees.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">OpenAI, at its core, doesn=E2=80=99t need any of that. It=E2=80=99s not m=
otivated by money, as an entity; it=E2=80=99s motivated by the good of huma=
nity.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So there=E2=80=99s a trade: =
OpenAI can raise money (and attract employees) for=C2=A0its grand project b=
y distributing the intermediate spoils to investors and employees. OpenAI d=
oesn=E2=80=99t want those spoils. It just wants the ultimate goal, the AGI,=
 which it will use benevolently to usher in a golden age for humanity.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am exaggerating in places, and I am not sayi=
ng that any of this is <em>correct</em>. I am just saying that, from the ou=
tside, this model seems to explain a lot of OpenAI=E2=80=99s choices. We ha=
ve talked about many of them:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
